fields.bio:
The von Rochmanns were Bankers and Merchants in Senjen, Norway.

When Peder came to the United States, he changed his name to Danielson - Daniel, being his fathers name and he, being Daniel's son. He later changed it to Rockman at the request of one of his brothers. It was needed to settle the estate in Norway.
Jeffery was Michele's son from a previous marriage
Randy was Annva's son from a previous marriage.
Timothy was Annva's son from a previous marriage.

Lyle, as my people call him, joined the Navy during World War II. Married Christine Delphine Kessler on February 18, 1933. Owned and operated the Mosinee IGA grocery store for many years. Later he also owned and operated Copps IGA grocery stores in Black River Falls and Stevens Point. He was a member of the American Legion and the Mosinee Masonic Lodge No. 318. He was a member of the Mosinee Fire Department and later 
 became Fire Chief.

Christine Delphine was born to John & Rose (Vytlacil) Kessler. She worked at the grocery store in Mosinee which Lyle and her owned. Her sister Lillian was married to Lyle's brother Don. The two couples were very close and did a lot of traveling after Lyle and Don retired.

Lawrence or Larry lived in Wausau, Wisconsin. Moved with his parents and 5 brothers & sisters (at that time) to Stevens Point at the age of 7. Attended Saint Annes, Saint Josephs and Saint Stephens grade schools. Graduated from Pacelli High School in 1974. 

Worked for the Copps Corporation for 15 years as a Baker. Worked for his brother Scott at his catering business for a couple of years and later went to work for Consolidated Papers. In 2000 the Finnish Paper and Wood products company Stora Enso purchased Consolidated Papers.

Mary Lou was born to Robert & Gladys (Feltz) Flisakowski in Stevens Point, Wisconsin. Attended McDill 
			grade school, Ben Franklin Jr. High School and graduated from Stevens Point Area Senior High School in 
			1975. She started working at Saint Michael's Hospital in 1973 (while still in high school) and quit in 
			1979. Married Larry on September of 1979 and they moved to Oshkosh, Wisconsin. One year later they moved 
			back to Stevens Point and she was rehired by Saint Michael's Hospital.

Patricia owns "Point Loma Publishing", a nautical book company in San Diego and is a freelance writer for boating magazines. She has a BS degree in Communication and Journalism from SIU (Illinois). Along with her husband John Rains, they have authored 4 nautical guidebooks.
Patrica and Robert had no children

John E. Rains was born to John Rains and Virginia Billings. John owns Rains Yacht Delivery, skippering yachts from Florida thru the Panama Canal to California. 
He has a BS degree in Business from NIU (Iowa). John is a highly decorated combat infantryman from the Vietman War in 69-70.
Michael is a child from Laurie's previous marriage.
Andrew and Jessica are not married, but have been together for 18 years.
